The paper discusses deep neural networks and their ability to overfit to training set biases and label noises, which are common problems in machine learning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel meta-learning algorithm, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions class imbalance and corrupted label problems, which are common in natural language processing (cs.NE) and computational linguistics (cs.CL), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG and cs.CV, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CL.
